headline: Is Centene a Mispriced Opportunity After Sharp Share Price Slide and Strategy Shift?
summary: If you are wondering whether Centene is quietly turning into a value opportunity, you are not alone. This stock has slipped off a lot of radars just as its fundamentals and pricing are starting to look more interesting. Despite a tough longer term run with the share price down about 32.6% over the last year and 51.5% over three years, the stock has started to show some life recently, gaining around 2.3% over the last week and 7.1% over the last month even as it remains roughly 35.6% lower...

headline: Ambetter Health & Tampa Bay Buccaneers Launch "Stay Healthy, Stay in the Game" PSA Urging Floridians to Prioritize Preventive Care Before Year-End
summary: Ambetter Health, a company of Centene Corporation (NYSE:CNC) and a health insurance marketplace product offered through the federal Health Insurance Marketplace, and the Tampa Bay Buccaneers have teamed up to release a new public service announcement (PSA) titled "Stay Healthy, Stay in the Game," encouraging Floridians to take charge of their health by engaging in preventive care and prioritizing routine screenings and year-end checkups with their primary care physician.

headline: Sunshine Health Partners with Local Women Athletes to Champion Health Awareness
summary: Sunshine Health, a company of Centene Corporation (NYSE: CNC) and a leading managed care organization dedicated to improving the health and well-being of Floridians, announced it will partner with elite female athletes who are aligned with Sunshine Health's mission of improving the health of the community and who are motivated to help others prioritize health and well-being.

headline: Oscar Health Rises As GOP Moderates Rebel Over ACA
summary: Oscar Health rallied on Wednesday morning amid an intraparty GOP rebellion over ACA subsidies, though other S&P 500 health care stocks lost more ground.  Centene, the top ACA Marketplace insurer by membership, and HCA Healthcare, the largest U.S. hospital operator, fell for a third straight session, with much of the damage coming Tuesday as House Speaker Mike Johnson signaled he wouldn't allow a vote on a bipartisan compromise plan to extend the subsidies.  On Monday, Morgan Stanley downgraded HCA to underweight from equal weight on Monday, saying its high valuation is at a peak as Washington reins in growth of the ACA Marketplaces and Medicaid supplemental payments.
